HEADWORD: establishmentarian
<hw>es*tab`lish*men*ta"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One
who regards the Church primarily as an establishment formed by the
State, and overlooks its intrinsic spiritual character.</def>
<rj><au>Shipley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

